==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Erse
<hw>Erse</hw> <pr>(⟦etil⟧rs)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[A modification of
<ets>Irish</ets>, OE. <ets>Irishe</ets>.]</ety> <def>A name sometimes
given to that dialect of the Celtic which is spoken in the Highlands of
Scotland; -- called, by the Highlanders,
<altname>Gaelic</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Erse</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Erse
<hw>Erse</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to the Celtic race in
the Highlands of Scotland, or to their language.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ersh</ent>⟦br⟧
